issue.title: [Rust] Hang / failure in CI on AMD64 Debian 10 Rust stable test workspace
issue.body:
***Note**: This issue was originally created as [ARROW-11896](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896). Please see the [migration documentation](https://gist.github.com/toddfarmer/12aa88361532d21902818a6044fda4c3) for further details.*

### Original Issue Description:
As observed first by [~nevi_me] on https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/9592#issuecomment-791901636

The Rust CI tests seem to be failing due to a timeout, due to a timeout . For example: https://github.com/apache/arrow/runs/2045186826 

Data from [~nevi_me]


```Java

running 17 tests

```

***Note**: [Comment](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896?focusedCommentId=17296532) by Andrew Lamb (alamb):*
I plan to look into this but will not have time until tomorrow

***Note**: [Comment](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896?focusedCommentId=17296535) by Andrew Lamb (alamb):*
Datapoint:

When running `cargo test --all` locally (on macos):
- as of  479dce5c790d0d31e1920d24a74b85d98510fc02, the tests all pass for me locally 
- as of bfa99d98e6f0b49aed079d9f99668390f84a933f (latest master at time of this writing)
  
  Here is my  [Cargo.lock](Cargo.lock) in case that is relevant

***Note**: [Comment](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896?focusedCommentId=17296537) by Andrew Lamb (alamb):*
After a `cargo update` the tests still pass for me locally

***Note**: [Comment](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896?focusedCommentId=17296791) by Neville Dipale (nevi_me):*
I've also run cargo test --all on a Windows machine, Linux machine, and Linux via WSL. In all instances, I ran cargo update.
We're either hanging at doc tests, or there's something else happening with the CI environment.

***Note**: [Comment](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896?focusedCommentId=17296843) by Andrew Lamb (alamb):*
## Timeline

I took a review of commits on https://github.com/apache/arrow/commits/master

https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/4f6adc700d1cebc50a0594b5aa671f64491cc20e: This is the last Rust commit where all CI checks passed 
Link to pass CI: https://github.com/apache/arrow/runs/2034747838 (AMD64 Debian 10 Rust stable test workspace; succeeded 3 days ago in 16m 31s)

https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/dec5ab9677a0dfb9e324a57ccf5550217a2117be: First  Rust commit on where a CI check failed
Fails in clippy (the tests are working): https://github.com/apache/arrow/runs/2043258080 (which makes me suspicious that  that maybe something in the tool chains got upgraded??)

https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/e2c7d9590a2b9f9a63c3d32ae6db44a5fbb114d4: This is the next Rust commit, CI still failing (on clippy0
Still fails on clippy: https://github.com/apache/arrow/runs/2043298275

https://github.com/apache/arrow/commit/bfa99d98e6f0b49aed079d9f99668390f84a933f: This is the next rust commit on master where we fix clippy
Now we see a new failure on "AMD64 Debian 10 Rust stable test workspace" – https://github.com/apache/arrow/runs/2045186826. However, I can't figure out how to get the logs from that job from github, so I made my own job

***Note**: [Comment](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ARROW-11896?focusedCommentId=17296844) by Andrew Lamb (alamb):*
I made a PR to see if I can debug a little more what was going on https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/9651

It seems to deliver the logs to the UI while I have the page open, so I got to see what actually failed

In this case, https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/9651/checks?check_run_id=2050214995, it was one of the parquet doctests fals failing in the parquet doctests (perhaps the linker is killed due to memory or something)?
